# 2️⃣ CHINA MACRO CYCLE — CREDIT DRIVES EVERYTHING

![Image](https://d1-invdn-com.investing.com/content/pic91be988f089576700381a953f3f0783d.png?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

![Image](https://cdn.macromicro.me/discuss/a2f11d71-502478.png?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

China’s macro cycle = **credit cycle**, not business cycle.

## **Credit Impulse (CI)**

The single most important macro indicator for China.

* **Leads global PMIs by ~9 months**
* **Drives commodities (copper, iron ore)**
* **Drives AUD, NZD, KRW**
* **Drives EM assets**
* **Correlated with global inflation swings**

When **CI turns up** → go long:

* AUD, NZD, KRW
* Copper, iron ore
* Chinese high yield (if no property stress)
* EM FX high beta
* Steepeners in global curves

When **CI turns down** → short:

* Metals
* EM beta
* CNY correlation trades
* Property equities

---

# 3️⃣ PROPERTY SECTOR — CHINA’S TRUE BUSINESS CYCLE

China’s property sector = ~25–30% of GDP (direct + indirect).

## **Key signals to monitor:**

* **Land sales** (crucial for LGFV financing)
* **New home starts**
* **Property developer bond spreads**
* **Mortgage rate cuts & relaxation**
* **Tier-1 vs Tier-3 housing price divergence**
* **Housing inventories**

**If property stabilizes → CNY strengthens, equities rally, curves steepen.**
**If property deteriorates → CNH weakens, credit stress rises, PBoC injects liquidity.**

